<div class="content-title">
<h3><a href="index.php?itemid=159">The Wanderer walking tours and memorial</a></h3>
</div>
Erik Calonius author of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWanderer-American-Slave-Conspiracy-Sails%2Fdp%2F0312343477&tag=the18thmassac-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325"> "The Wanderer, the Last American Slave Ship and the Conspiracy That Set its Sails"</a>, sent a note to let us know that groups in Savannah are planning a walking tour with hopes of an April starting date and the creation of a memorial to The Wanderer and those stolen from their homeland.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWanderer-American-Slave-Conspiracy-Sails%2Fdp%2F0312343477&tag=the18thmassac-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325"><br />
