<div class="content-title">
<h3><a href="index.php?itemid=136">More on Samuel Jordan</a></h3>
</div>
With Donald’s post yesterday on Samuel Jordan, I thought it only fitting to bring up two posts from the past.<br />
<br />
In July, the Milford Daily News <a href="http://www.18thmass.com/blog/index.php?itemid=49">ran an article about Samuel Jordan a</a>nd his service to his nation. To say it was a hatchet job with an agenda would be too kind. We reprinted the article at this link and also w<a href="http://www.18thmass.com/blog/index.php?itemid=50">rote a letter to the editor</a> that explored Jordan and his true feelings – not the ones that the article’s author came up with. <br />
<br />
Sadly, they never printed the letter. Luckily, we still have it. So here they are for you to enjoy.<br />
<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.18thmass.com/blog/index.php?itemid=49">Click here for the original article.</a><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.18thmass.com/blog/index.php?itemid=50">Click here for the letter to the editor.</a>


